==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commeasurable
<hw>Com*meas"ur*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Commensurable</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the same measure;
commensurate; proportional.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She being now removed by death, a <qex>commeasurable</qex> grief
took as full possession of him as joy had done.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Walton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commeasure</ent>⟦br⟧
